https://192.168.1.1/securechangeworkflow/api/securechange/users|Demonstrates how to implicitly imports LDAP users as automatics users to SecureChange:
&lt;user xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:type="user"&gt;
	&lt;name&gt;ldap_name&lt;/name&gt;
	&lt;origin_type&gt;LDAP&lt;/origin_type&gt;
		&lt;ldap_configuration&gt;
			&lt;id&gt;1&lt;/id&gt;
		&lt;/ldap_configuration&gt;
&lt;/user&gt;

https://192.168.1.1/securechangeworkflow/api/securechange/users|Demonstrates how to create a new local user in SecureChange:
&lt;localuser&gt;
	&lt;name&gt;new user name&lt;/name&gt;
	&lt;password&gt;pa$$w0rd&lt;/password&gt;
	&lt;first_name&gt;John&lt;/first_name&gt;
	&lt;last_name&gt;Doe&lt;/last_name&gt;
	&lt;email&gt;john.doe@mail.com&lt;/email&gt;
	&lt;phone&gt;(555) 555-1234&lt;/phone&gt;
	&lt;notes&gt;some notes&lt;/notes&gt;
	&lt;default_authentication&gt;false&lt;/default_authentication&gt;
&lt;/localuser&gt;
